cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.RO, cs.CV, cs.MM

This paper discusses the use of communication technologies for vehicle-to-vehicle (V2V) communication, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also proposes a compensation mechanism to counteract misalignments induced by vehicle dynamics, which involves control and robotics (cs.RO). The use of Free-Space Optics (FSO) and Radio-Frequency (RF) technologies also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM).
